QeMeFbaSrN_w2n7czQrLq1G_PdZ73Z_QEaKxC_jLCF5iX47GGSLkKtyPBqtOofpBKSYVGy4DVZm=
Uw8C5kKSSfaqp-A_9A7DAkf4" rel=3D"" style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration=
: underline;">Axie Infinity</a>. Axie is neither the most fun game in the w=
orld nor the highest-paying job in the world, but it was able to attract ov=
er a million players because it offered more money than the games they were=
 used to playing, and more fun (and often money) than the other jobs availa=
ble to them. If players&#8217; old games were 7 on fun and 1 on money, and =
their old jobs were 2 on fun and 4 on money, Axie&#8217;s 5 on fun and 6 on=
 money pushed the funtier out.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-si=
ze: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">Web3 gaming isn&#8217;t fi=
nished here. The space will evolve along those two dimensions: fun and mone=
y. New games, and improvements from Axie itself, will focus on both tokenom=
ic designs that make players more money and game designs that make the game=
s more fun to play.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; l=
ine-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">In <em><a href=3D"https://email.mg2.s=
